ncy plan for your contingency plans, and it isn't paranoia — it's love wearing armor."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"black_widow","result_name":"Black Widow","result_emoji":"🕷️","result_data":{"name":"Black Widow","emoji":"🕷️","tagline":"The Quiet Ledger","key":"black_widow","description":"You read every room twice before it reads you once, and you keep your cards so close that most people don't realize you're playing."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"blackpanther","result_name":"Black Panther","result_emoji":"🐆","result_data":{"name":"Black Panther","emoji":"🐆","tagline":"The Composed Crown","key":"blackpanther","description":"You move through the world with a composure that makes people straighten up a little when you enter the room."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"cap","result_name":"Captain America","result_emoji":"⭐","result_data":{"name":"Captain America","emoji":"⭐","tagline":"The Compass That Holds","key":"cap","description":"You're the person others check themselves against — not because you preach, but because you do the right thing with unnerving consistency, especially when it's unpopular."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"captain_marvel","result_name":"Captain Marvel","result_emoji":"🌟","result_data":{"name":"Captain Marvel","emoji":"🌟","tagline":"The Engine Without Limits","key":"captain_marvel","description":"You've spent your whole life being told where the ceiling is, and getting up anyway became your signature move."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"doctor_strange","result_name":"Doctor Strange","result_emoji":"🔮","result_data":{"name":"Doctor Strange","emoji":"🔮","tagline":"The Keeper of Unseen Doors","key":"doctor_strange","description":"You were brilliant first and wise second, and the tuition for that second lesson cost you almost everything."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"flash","result_name":"The Flash","result_emoji":"⚡","result_data":{"name":"The Flash","emoji":"⚡","tagline":"The Lightning That Laughs","key":"flash","description":"You move through life at a sprint and still notice everyone in it — quick with help, quicker with a joke, first to arrive even when you left last."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"green_lantern","result_name":"Green Lantern","result_emoji":"🟢","result_data":{"name":"Green Lantern","emoji":"🟢","tagline":"The Will Made Light","key":"green_lantern","description":"Fear tells everyone where to stop, and you treat that line as a starting suggestion."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"hulk","result_name":"Hulk","result_emoji":"💚","result_data":{"name":"Hulk","emoji":"💚","tagline":"The Gentle Earthquake","key":"hulk","description":"You contain multitudes: a thoughtful, brilliant inner life and feelings powerful enough to rearrange furniture."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"ironman","result_name":"Iron Man","result_emoji":"⚙️","result_data":{"name":"Iron Man","emoji":"⚙️","tagline":"The Self-Built Tomorrow","key":"ironman","description":"Your brain runs at a clock speed that makes waiting physically painful, so you build instead: prototypes, plans, comebacks, whole futures."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"ms_marvel","result_name":"Ms. Marvel","result_emoji":"✨","result_data":{"name":"Ms. Marvel","emoji":"✨","tagline":"The Fangirl Ascendant","key":"ms_marvel","description":"You grew up studying heroes the way other people study for finals, and it turns out all that devotion was secretly training."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"spiderman","result_name":"Spider-Man","result_emoji":"🕸️","result_data":{"name":"Spider-Man","emoji":"🕸️","tagline":"The Friendly Neighborhood Heart","key":"spiderman","description":"You're perpetually overbooked, slightly late, and still somehow the person who never actually lets anyone down."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"storm","result_name":"Storm","result_emoji":"🌩️","result_data":{"name":"Storm","emoji":"🌩️","tagline":"The Regal Tempest","key":"storm","description":"You carry a calm that other people borrow in a crisis, and an authority you never have to raise your voice to prove."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"superman","result_name":"Superman","result_emoji":"☀️","result_data":{"name":"Superman","emoji":"☀️","tagline":"The Hope on the Horizon","key":"superman","description":"You could cut every corner — you're that capable — and it genuinely never occurs to you."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"thor","result_name":"Thor","result_emoji":"🔨","result_data":{"name":"Thor","emoji":"🔨","tagline":"The Thunder With a Grin","key":"thor","description":"You arrive like weather — loud, magnificent, impossible to ignore — and you love every second of it."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"wolverine","result_name":"Wolverine","result_emoji":"🦡","result_data":{"name":"Wolverine","emoji":"🦡","tagline":"The Reluctant Blade","key":"wolverine","description":"You've been through more than you'll ever say, and you cope by pretending you don't care — right up until someone needs you, which blows your cover every time."}},{"quiz_type":"superhero","result_key":"wonderwoman","result_name":"Wonder Woman","result_emoji":"🛡️","result_data":{"name":"Wonder Woman","emoji":"🛡️","tagline":"The Truth Unsheathed","key":"wonderwoman","description":"You lead with truth the way other people lead with small talk, and injustice in front of you is automatically your business."}},{"quiz_type":"values","result_key":"achievement","result_name":"The Achiever","result_emoji":"🏆","result_data":{"name":"The Achiever","emoji":"🏆","tagline":"The Undeniable Standard","key":"achievement","description":"You feel most alive when you're measurably getting better at something hard, and a goal without a scoreboard barely counts as a goal."}},{"quiz_type":"values","result_key":"benevolence","result_name":"The Caregiver","result_emoji":"💗","result_data":{"name":"The Caregiver","emoji":"💗","tagline":"The Inner-Circle Keeper","key":"benevolence","description":"You measure a life by whether the people who count on you could always count on you — and yours can."}},{"quiz_type":"values","result_key":"security","result_name":"The Guardian","result_emoji":"🛡️","result_data":{"name":"The Guardian","emoji":"🛡️","tagline":"The Solid Ground","key":"security","description":"While everyone else chases upside, you're the one asking the unglamorous questions about downside — and you're usually right to."}},{"quiz_type":"values","result_key":"selfdirection","result_name":"The Trailblazer","result_emoji":"🧭","result_data":{"name":"The Trailblazer","emoji":"🧭","tagline":"The Compass of One","key":"selfdirection","description":"You need to think your own thoughts, make your own calls, and live by conclusions you actually reached yourself."}},{"quiz_type":"values","result_key":"stimulation","result_name":"The Adventurer","result_emoji":"⚡","result_data":{"name":"The Adventurer","emoji":"⚡","tagline":"The Spark Chaser","key":"stimulation","description":"Routine drains you faster than hard work ever could; your real nightmare isn't failure, it's a life that becomes a repeating loop."}},{"quiz_type":"values","result_key":"universalism","result_name":"The Humanitarian","result_emoji":"🌍","result_data":{"name":"The Humanitarian","emoji":"🌍","tagline":"The Wider Circle","key":"universalism","description":"Your conscience has a longer range than most — it reaches past your own circle to strangers, other species, and the planet itself."}}]$share_catalog$::jsonb
  ) AS row_data (
    quiz_type text,
    result_key text,
    result_name text,
    result_emoji text,
    result_data jsonb
  )
)
INSERT INTO public.share_result_catalog (
  quiz_type,
  result_key,
  result_name,
  result_emoji,
  result_data
)
SELECT quiz_type, result_key, result_name, result_emoji, result_data
FROM catalog
ON CONFLICT (quiz_type, result_key) DO UPDATE
SET result_name = EXCLUDED.result_name,
    result_emoji = EXCLUDED.result_emoji,
    result_data = EXCLUDED.result_data;

-- ─── Validated share creation ──────────────────────────────────────────────

DROP POLICY IF EXISTS "anyone can create shared results" ON public.shared_results;
REVOKE INSERT ON TABLE public.shared_results FROM anon, authenticated;

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.create_shared_result(
  p_quiz_type text,
  p_result_key text,
  p_scores jsonb DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb
)
RETURNS text
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path = ''
AS $$
DECLARE
  catalog_row public.share_result_catalog%ROWTYPE;
  clean_scores jsonb := '{}'::jsonb;
  score_count integer;
  share_id text;
  attempts integer := 0;
BEGIN
  IF p_quiz_type IS NULL
     OR p_quiz_type !~ '^[a-z][a-z0-9_-]{1,31}$'
     OR p_result_key IS NULL
     OR char_length(p_result_key) NOT BETWEEN 1 AND 20 THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Invalid quiz result'
      USING ERRCODE = 'invalid_parameter_value';
  END IF;

  SELECT * INTO catalog_row
  FROM public.share_result_catalog
  WHERE quiz_type = p_quiz_type
    AND result_key = p_result_key;

  IF NOT FOUND THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Unknown quiz result'
      USING ERRCODE = 'invalid_parameter_value';
  END IF;

  IF p_scores IS NULL THEN
    p_scores := '{}'::jsonb;
  END IF;
  IF jsonb_typeof(p_scores) <> 'object' THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Scores must be a JSON object'
      USING ERRCODE = 'invalid_parameter_value';
  END IF;

  SELECT count(*) INTO score_count FROM jsonb_object_keys(p_scores);
  IF score_count > 12 OR EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM jsonb_each(p_scores) AS score
    WHERE score.key !~ '^[A-Za-z0-9]{1,4}$'
       OR jsonb_typeof(score.value) <> 'number'
       OR abs((score.value::text)::numeric) > 1000
  ) THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Invalid score payload'
      USING ERRCODE = 'invalid_parameter_value';
  END IF;

  IF p_quiz_type = 'big5' AND (
    score_count <> 5
    OR EXISTS (
      SELECT 1
      FROM jsonb_each(p_scores) AS score
      WHERE score.key NOT IN ('O', 'C', 'E', 'A', 'N')
         OR (score.value::text)::numeric NOT BETWEEN 0 AND 100
    )
  ) THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Invalid Big Five scores'
      USING ERRCODE = 'invalid_parameter_value';
  END IF;

  IF score_count > 0 THEN
    SELECT jsonb_object_agg(score.key, round((score.value::text)::numeric, 2))
    INTO clean_scores
    FROM jsonb_each(p_scores) AS score;
  END IF;

  LOOP
    attempts := attempts + 1;
    share_id := replace(gen_random_uuid()::text, '-', '');
    BEGIN
      INSERT INTO public.shared_results (
        id,
        quiz_type,
        result_key,
        result_name,
        result_emoji,
        result_data,
        owner_id
      )
      VALUES (
        share_id,
        catalog_row.quiz_type,
        catalog_row.result_key,
        catalog_row.result_name,
        catalog_row.result_emoji,
        catalog_row.result_data
          || CASE
               WHEN score_count > 0 THEN jsonb_build_object('scores', clean_scores)
               ELSE '{}'::jsonb
             END,
        auth.uid()
      );
      EXIT;
    EXCEPTION WHEN unique_violation THEN
      IF attempts >= 3 THEN RAISE; END IF;
    END;
  END LOOP;

  RETURN share_id;
END;
$$;

REVOKE EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.create_shared_result(text, text, jsonb) FROM PUBLIC;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.create_shared_result(text, text, jsonb) TO anon, authenticated;

-- ─── Strong share reads and permanent deployment canary ────────────────────

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.get_shared_result(p_id text)
RETURNS TABLE (
  id text,
  quiz_type text,
  result_key text,
  result_name text,
  result_emoji text,
  result_data jsonb,
  view_count integer,
  created_at timestamptz,
  has_owner boolean,
  owner_is_me boolean,
  connection_status text
)
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path = ''
AS $$
DECLARE
  client_ip text;
BEGIN
  IF p_id IS NULL OR p_id !~ '^[a-f0-9]{32}$' THEN
    RETURN;
  END IF;

  client_ip := public.request_client_ip();
  IF client_ip IS NOT NULL
     AND NOT public.check_rate_limit('share_read', client_ip, 120, 60) THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Too many shared-result requests'
      USING ERRCODE = 'P0001';
  END IF;

  RETURN QUERY
  SELECT
    s.id, s.quiz_type, s.result_key, s.result_name, s.result_emoji,
    s.result_data, s.view_count, s.created_at,
    (s.owner_id IS NOT NULL) AS has_owner,
    (auth.uid() IS NOT NULL AND s.owner_id = auth.uid()) AS owner_is_me,
    (
      SELECT CASE
        WHEN c.status = 'accepted' THEN 'accepted'
        WHEN c.requester = auth.uid() THEN 'pending_sent'
        ELSE 'pending_received'
      END
      FROM public.connections c
      WHERE auth.uid() IS NOT NULL
        AND s.owner_id IS NOT NULL
        AND ((c.requester = auth.uid() AND c.addressee = s.owner_id)
          OR (c.requester = s.owner_id AND c.addressee = auth.uid()))
      LIMIT 1
    ) AS connection_status
  FROM public.shared_results s
  WHERE s.id = p_id
  LIMIT 1;
END;
$$;

REVOKE EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.get_shared_result(text) FROM PUBLIC;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.get_shared_result(text) TO anon, authenticated;

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.increment_shared_result_views(p_id text)
RETURNS void
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path = ''
AS $$
BEGIN
  IF p_id IS NULL OR p_id !~ '^[a-f0-9]{32}$' THEN RETURN; END IF;
  IF NOT public.check_rate_limit('view_increment', p_id, 10, 60) THEN RETURN; END IF;

  UPDATE public.shared_results
  SET view_count = view_count + 1
  WHERE id = p_id;
END;
$$;

REVOKE EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.increment_shared_result_views(text) FROM PUBLIC;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.increment_shared_result_views(text) TO anon, authenticated;

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.request_connection(p_share_id text)
RETURNS text
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path = ''
AS $$
DECLARE
  v_owner uuid;
  v_quiz text;
  v_existing public.connections%ROWTYPE;
  inserted_count integer;
BEGIN
  IF auth.uid() IS NULL THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Sign in to add someone to your circle'
      USING ERRCODE = 'insufficient_privilege';
  END IF;
  IF p_share_id IS NULL OR p_share_id !~ '^[a-f0-9]{32}$' THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Invalid share link' USING ERRCODE = 'invalid_parameter_value';
  END IF;

  SELECT owner_id, quiz_type INTO v_owner, v_quiz
  FROM public.shared_results WHERE id = p_share_id;
  IF v_owner IS NULL THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'This share link cannot receive circle requests'
      USING ERRCODE = 'invalid_parameter_value';
  END IF;
  IF v_owner = auth.uid() THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'That is your own result' USING ERRCODE = 'invalid_parameter_value';
  END IF;

  SELECT * INTO v_existing FROM public.connections c
  WHERE (c.requester = auth.uid() AND c.addressee = v_owner)
     OR (c.requester = v_owner AND c.addressee = auth.uid());
  IF FOUND THEN
    RETURN CASE
      WHEN v_existing.status = 'accepted' THEN 'accepted'
      WHEN v_existing.requester = auth.uid() THEN 'pending_sent'
      ELSE 'pending_received'
    END;
  END IF;

  IF NOT public.check_rate_limit('circle_request', auth.uid()::text, 10, 60) THEN
    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Too many circle requests. Please try again shortly.'
      USING ERRCODE = 'P0001';
  END IF;

  INSERT INTO public.connections (requester, addressee, share_id, quiz_type)
  VALUES (auth.uid(), v_owner, p_share_id, v_quiz)
  ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
  GET DIAGNOSTICS inserted_count = ROW_COUNT;

  IF inserted_count = 0 THEN
    SELECT * INTO v_existing FROM public.connections c
    WHERE (c.requester = auth.uid() AND c.addressee = v_owner)
       OR (c.requester = v_owner AND c.addressee = auth.uid());
    RETURN CASE
      WHEN v_existing.status = 'accepted' THEN 'accepted'
      WHEN v_existing.requester = auth.uid() THEN 'pending_sent'
      ELSE 'pending_received'
    END;
  END IF;

  RETURN 'pending_sent';
END;
$$;

REVOKE EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.request_connection(text) FROM PUBLIC, anon;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.request_connection(text) TO authenticated;

INSERT INTO public.shared_results (
  id,
  quiz_type,
  result_key,
  result_name,
  result_emoji,
  result_data,
  owner_id
)
SELECT
  '0000000000000000000000000000cafe',
  catalog.quiz_type,
  catalog.result_key,
  catalog.result_name,
  catalog.result_emoji,
  catalog.result_data || jsonb_build_object(
    'scores',
    jsonb_build_object('O', 50, 'C', 50, 'E', 50, 'A', 50, 'N', 50)
  ),
  NULL
FROM public.share_result_catalog AS catalog
WHERE catalog.quiz_type = 'big5' AND catalog.result_key = 'profile'
ON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE
SET quiz_type = EXCLUDED.quiz_type,
    result_key = EXCLUDED.result_key,
    result_name = EXCLUDED.result_name,
    result_emoji = EXCLUDED.result_emoji,
    result_data = EXCLUDED.result_data,
    owner_id = NULL;

-- ─── Close unused subscriber writes ────────────────────────────────────────

DROP POLICY IF EXISTS "email_subscribers_insert_anon" ON public.email_subscribers;
DROP POLICY IF EXISTS "email_subscribers_insert_authenticated" ON public.email_subscribers;
REVOKE INSERT ON TABLE public.email_subscribers FROM anon, authenticated;

-- ─── Account-bound quiz ratings ────────────────────────────────────────────

DROP POLICY IF EXISTS "feedback_insert_anon" ON public.quiz_feedback;
DROP POLICY IF EXISTS "feedback_insert_authenticated" ON public.quiz_feedback;
REVOKE INSERT ON TABLE public.quiz_feedback FROM anon;
GRANT INSERT ON TABLE public.quiz_feedback TO authenticated;

DELETE FROM public.quiz_feedback AS old_rating
USING public.quiz_feedback AS newer_rating
WHERE old_rating.user_id IS NOT NULL
  AND old_rating.user_id = newer_rating.user_id
  AND old_rating.quiz_key = newer_rating.quiz_key
  AND old_rating.id < newer_rating.id;

CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_quiz_feedback_user_quiz
  ON public.quiz_feedback (user_id, quiz_key)
  WHERE user_id IS NOT NULL;

CREATE POLICY "feedback_insert_authenticated"
  ON public.quiz_feedback
  FOR INSERT
  TO authenticated
  WITH CHECK (user_id = auth.uid());

-- ─── Data retention ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.prune_expired_product_data()
RETURNS trigger
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path = ''
AS $$
BEGIN
  DELETE FROM public.analytics_events
  WHERE created_at < now() - interval '12 months';

  DELETE FROM public.quiz_feedback
  WHERE created_at < now() - interval '12 months';

  DELETE FROM public.rate_limit_log
  WHERE created_at < now() - interval '10 minutes';

  RETURN NULL;
END;
$$;

DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS trg_prune_expired_product_data ON public.analytics_events;
CREATE TRIGGER trg_prune_expired_product_data
  AFTER INSERT ON public.analytics_events
  FOR EACH STATEMENT
  EXECUTE FUNCTION public.prune_expired_product_data();

REVOKE EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.prune_expired_product_data() FROM PUBLIC, anon, authenticated;
